Alastair Cook admitted he is disappointed not to be going to the World Cup in February after being stripped of England's one-day captaincy.

The 29-year-old is frustrated to be missing England's campaign in Australia and New Zealand after his poor form and a dismal series in Sri Lanka led to him being replaced by Eoin Morgan.

Speaking at Alexandra Palace, where Cook took on Jimmy Anderson in a one-leg darts challenge before commentating for Sky Sports, he said: 'Sometimes these things happen.

